%N A064631 4^n = x*3^n+y*2^n+z*1^n, so 4^n equals the sum of a(n)=x+y+z pieces of like powers (=length of right side of solution of this Diophantine equation). Length of solutions obtained with "greedy algorithm" are given in A064630[n]. Here the binary order [A029837] of the length of those solutions is displayed, which "on the average" nearly equals n.
%C A064631 a(n)<=n and near to n.
%C A064631 a(n)=n for n = {1, 3, 4, 5, 7, 10, 11, 12, 13, 14, 15, 16, 22, 25, 28, 31, 32, 33, 34, 35, 36, 37, 39, 40, 42, 44, 46, 49, 50, 51, 54, 55, 57, 59, 60, 63, 64, 66, 70, 72, 75, 78, 79, 82, 87, 88, 89, 90, 93, 94, 95, 97, 98, 99, 100}.
%F A064631 a(n) = A029837(A064630(n)) = ceiling(log_2(A064630(n)).
